Title: 13-inch MacBook Pro Replacement Battery (Mid 2009 to Mid 2012) A1278
Body (HTML):
Replacement battery for 13-inch MacBook Pro (Mid 2009 to Mid 2012). This battery is designed for the following MacBook Pro Models: MB990LL/A, MB991LL/A, MC374LL/A, MC375LL/A, MC700LL/A, MC724LL/A, MD314LL/A, MD313LL/A, MD101LL/A, MD102LL/A.

Give Your MacBook a Second Life
Over time, your laptop battery continues to lose its ability to charge, making it difficult to use it anywhere there isn't a power source. A new battery can lend a new lease on life to your laptop, giving you the flexibility to work or play on the go.

Compatible & Reliable
Ramjet Mac Batteries have been designed and engineered to fit seamlessly into your Mac just like the original battery. We've rigorously tested and certified our batteries to make sure they work perfectly for you, just like we've done with our industry-leading Mac Memory and other products since 1996.

Fully Supported & Guaranteed
If you have any questions about installing or using your new battery, our customer-support team are real experts and happy to assist. Your purchase also comes with a 30-day guarantee, during which time you can easily exchange or return your purchase (visit our Returns section for details).

Environmentally Responsible
In an ongoing effort to avoid toxic waste, we've provided links to local resources to help safely dispose of your old battery. Or if you prefer, we can take it off your hands and recycle it ourselves. See below for more details.

Contact any of these local resources to recycle your old battery or an old machine.

www.Call2Recycle.org / 1-800-8-Battery
www.RecyclingCenters.org
www. Earth911.com / 1-800-Cleanup

Title: Xserve Memory for Model 3,1 (2GB)
Body (HTML):
The Xserve DDR3-1066 comes in two versions, the 4-core and the 8-core. The 4-core has 6 DIMM slots, and it upgradable to a maximum of 24GB with the installation of 6x 4GB modules (2x 12GB kits). The 8-core has 12 slots, and it is upgradable to a maximum of 48GB with the installation of 12x 4GB modules (4x 12GB kits). Since the new Xserve runs a "Tri-Channel" memory interface, memory MUST be installed in matched sets of three at a time.

Matched Modules: The new Xserve Intel DDR3-1066 runs a Tri-Channel memory interface. The Ramjet kits for the Xserve DDR3-1066 contain a matched set (3x) of DIMMs. The kit will consist of identical brand/model/spec IC's. They will be from a single batch, and will have matching series numbers. This ensures maximum performance, and perfect compatibility.

Please view Apple's installation guide for more information.
Apple's installation guide.

Title: Ramjet 2TB SATA III 2.5-inch Internal SSD + Mac Pro Adapter
Body (HTML):
SSDs Optimized for your Mac Pro

Our 6Gb/s SATA III 2.5-inch Internal Solid State Drives are designed for your Mac Pro, with read speeds operating at 550 MB/s. A typical 7200 RPM rotating hard drive runs at 20-80 MB/s. Simplicity is key -- every Ramjet SSD comes with an easy upgrade kit that can be done in 3 simple steps. The upgrade kit includes:

  • 2.5" to 3.5" drive bay adapter for your Mac Pro
  • Cloning software CD
  • Mac ready tools (screwdriver)

Our Mac Pro SSD kits also include a 2.5" to 3.5" adapter for easy installation in any of your Mac Pro drive bays.

10x the Reliability

A Ramjet SSD is built with flash chips so there are no moving parts. That means:

  • Less mechanical failure
  • More resistant to shock and vibration than rotating hard drives
  • Quieter operation
  • Less heat generated than rotating hard drives

Title: Mac Pro Ultra PCI Express Card with 1TB SSD
Body (HTML):
Our PCI Express card is compatible with Apple's Mac Pro 2008-2012 towers. You can mount any 2.5" Mac compatible SATA III SSD onto this adapter card.

By taking advantage of your Mac Pro's quicker PCI Express bus, you can substantially increase the access time over your conventional SATA II drive bays. The drive bays in a Mac Pro are limited to 275/255 Mbps read/write speeds. This adapter/drive combination is capable of 550 Mbps read/write speeds, depending upon the speed of your SSD.

This drive adapter is bootable, making for the quickest possible system performance. Please note that using this kit for your boot drive adds a 10-15 second delay to boot time. If you are using the kit for a data drive (a non-boot volume), the delay will not be added.

Compatible Mac Pros:Â Mac Model ID 3,1 - 4,1 - 5,1. This PCIe card is NOT compatible with Apple's latest Mac Pro 6,1 released in Late 2013.

Interface:Â PCI Express 2.0

Quick FAQ:Â Windows is supported by this device. 3.5" drives are not supported on this card.
Image Alt Text: 1TB SSD for Apple Mac Pro - PCI Express

Title: Mac Pro PCI Express Card with 2x1TB SSD
Body (HTML):
Our PCI Express card/SSD Combo is compatible with Apple's Mac Pro 2006-2012 towers. For this kit, we mount one of our blazing fast 550 Mbps 1TB 2.5-inch Solid State Drives is mounted onto our PCIE adapter card.

By taking advantage of your Mac Pro's quicker PCI Express bus, you can substantially increase the access time over your conventional SATA II drive bays. The drive bays in a Mac Pro are limited to 275/255 Mbps read/write speeds. This adapter/drive combination is capable of 450/350 Mbps read/write speeds!

This drive adapter is bootable, making for the quickest possible system performance.

Compatible Mac Pros:Â Mac Model ID 1,1 - 2,1 - 3,1 - 4,1 - 5,1. Â This PCIe card is NOT compatible with Apple's latest Mac Pro 6,1 released in Late 2013.

Interface:Â PCI Express 2.0

Quick FAQ:Â Windows is supported by this device. 3.5" drives are not supported on this card

Title: Xserve Memory for Model 3,1 (8GBx3)
Body (HTML):
The Xserve 3,1 DDR3-1066 comes in two versions, the 4-core and the 8-core. The 4-core has 6 DIMM slots, and it upgradable to a maximum of 24GB with the installation of 6x 4GB modules (2x 12GB kits). The 8-core has 12 slots, and it is upgradable to a maximum of 48GB with the installation of 12x 4GB modules (4x 12GB kits). Since the new Xserve runs a "Tri-Channel" memory interface, memory MUST be installed in matched sets of three at a time.

Matched Modules: The Xserve 3,1 is based on the Intel's Xeon 5500 Series. It runs on a Tri-Channel memory interface. The Ramjet kits for the Xserve 3,1 DDR3-1066 contain a matched set (3x) of DIMMs. The kit will consist of identical brand/model/spec IC's. They will be from a single batch, and will have matching series numbers. This ensures maximum performance, and perfect compatibility.

Please view Apple's installation guide for more information.
Apple's installation guide.

Title: Xserve Memory for Model 2,1 (4GBx2)
Body (HTML):
The Xserve 2,1 is based on the Intel Xeon 5400 series CPU. Â This Xserve uses a new type of memory called an FB-DIMM. There are eight (8) slots, and the FB-DIMMs must be installed in pairs (2x at a time), or to run 256 Bit Addressing they would be installed in matched quads (4x identical modules). The original 1GB is installed as a pair of two 512MB FB-DIMMs. The system maximum is 32GB with the installation of eight (8) 4 GB FB-DIMMs.

Matched Modules: Ramjet kits contain a matched pair of FB-DIMMs. The kit will consist of identical brand/model/spec IC's. They will be from a single batch, and will have matching series numbers. This ensures perfect compatibility.

256 Bit Addressing: The Xserve 2,1 is capable of addressing a bank of four (4) FB-DIMMs as a single 256-bit memory bus. Having your memory installed as a matched quad will increase your system performance by 5-10%. The Ramjet 1GB FB-DIMM kit (2x 512MB) can be installed along with the Apple original 1GB (2x 512MB) to create a 256 bit quad of four (4) 512MB FB-DIMMs.Â 

Please view Apple's installation guide for more information.
Apple's installation guide.

Body (HTML):
400Mhz DDR vs. 533Mhz DDR2:
Do you have the "Original" G5 that runs 400Mhz DDR memory, or the "Dual Core" G5 that runs 533Mhz DDR2 memory? Refer to our DDR vs. DDR2 Guide.

ECC vs. Non-ECC:
ECC memory is usually used in mission critical applications like servers, but Apple is now making it available to G5 workstations! ECC stands for Error Correction Code. This type of memory uses an extra parity bit to detect and correct some types of memory errors. In order to run ECC, all installed DIMMs must be the ECC type. You can mix ECC and Non-ECC, but the ECC function will be disabled.

The G5 "Dual Core" runs 533Mhz DDR2 memory. These dual core G5s can come with either 1 or 2 processor cards that have two processors on each, and are Dual or Quad G5s. The dual core G5s have 8 memory slots which can each hold a maximum of 2GB, for a system maximum of 16GB.

Matched Sets:
In order to provide you with optimal performance and stability, all of our G5 kits are configured with matched modules.

Title: PowerMac G3 Pro Memory 32MB
Body (HTML):
The PowerMac G3 Pro also goes by the names G3 Yosemite, and G3 Blue & White.

Contrary to the Apple specification, the G3 Pro is able to use a maximum of 1024MB (1GB) in system memory.

Ramjet uses the more expensive 16x8 based IC chips in our G3 Pro 256MB modules. This insures better compatibility and performance over the cheaper 32x4 IC's that are used by many memory vendors.

For this application, Ramjet also uses a faster SDRAM type called PC-133, which has been configured to run at 100Mhz in the G3 Pro. This improves reliability, and will give you a small performance improvement over the slower PC-100.

Title: PowerMac G3 Beige Memory 32MB
Body (HTML): Contrary to the Apple specification, the PowerMac G3 beige models are able to use a maximum of 768MB in system memory with the installation of three 256MB DIMMs.Â

Title: PowerBook G4 Titanium Memory 256MB
Body (HTML):
The PowerBook G4 Titanium model has two memory slots which run PC-133 SO-DIMMs. The Titanium can recognize a maximum of 1Gig (1024mb). You can reach that maximum with the installation of two (2) 512mb SO-DIMMs.

Stacked v. non-stacked chips: A module built from stacked chips takes two RAM wafers and stacks them on top of each other. This makes it possible to build a large module (like a 512mb SDRAM SO-DIMM) using cheap low density parts. Stacked chip modules are bad because they draw more power, and have heat build-up problems. Ramjet only uses Lower Power Consumption non-stacked IC chips.

Title: PowerBook G4 Aluminum (DDR2) Memory 512MB
Body (HTML):
The PowerBook G4 Aluminum has used two different types of RAM during it's model run: DDR2 and DDR. These two memory types are not compatible with each other, so it is important to find out which type your PowerBook runs before you order. The earlier PowerBook G4 Aluminum models run DDR. The newer PowerBook G4 Aluminum released on Oct. 20, 2005 run DDR2.

For assistance in finding your RAM type, please look at our DDR vs. DDR2 Guide.


12" Model: One memory slot that can be upgraded with up to a 1Gig PC-2700 SO-DIMM. The original 128mb or 256mb that comes with this PowerBook is soldered on the main logic board, and is not removable.

15" and 17" Models: Two memory slots. The models released on Oct. 20, 2005 (M996LL/A and M9970LL/A) run DDR2, and the earlier models run DDR.

Bus Slewing: Some models of PowerBook G4 Aluminum use this feature which lowers the voltage to the memory when the PowerBook is on battery power. This conserves power. However, this also means that you need a special Bus Slewing compatible SO-DIMM that can handle an undervoltage properly. Ramjet SO-DIMMs for the PowerBook G4 Aluminum have the low voltage feature, and therefore the Ramjet modules here are Bus Slewing compatible.

Title: 480GB SSD Hard Drive
Body (HTML):
An SSD, or solid-state drive, can transform even sluggish Macs into powerful, efficient machines.

Hard drives are made up of several moving parts, which can only move so fast and have a tendency to break down over time. SSDs, however, use the more refined flash memoryâan increasingly affordable technology that comes with immeasurable perks.

Flash = Fast
We realize that every minute in your workday is valuable. An SSD runs so much faster than a hard drive that you'll actually notice a difference in how quickly your computer and applications boot. File searches and file transfers will speed up and you'll experience a major acceleration in video, audio and graphic rendering and editing time. Meanwhile, your computer will multitask more efficiently, as you notice a perceivable boost in the performance of programs such as Adobe Creative Suite, Final Cut Pro, ProTools, MS Office Suite and more. Ramjet SSDs use the fastest components available for Mac use including Sandforce flash memory controllers--the current gold standard--making our SSDs substantially faster than Apple factory SSDs, at about half the price.

10x the Reliability

Transporting your computer is safer since SSDs are substantially more resistant to shock and vibration than standard drives, and they experience far less mechanical failure. And since there are no moving parts here, they're also quieter and generate less heat than hard drives. Because the SSD truly is a marvel of technology, all of the above will run on less energy, thus extending your battery life.

Supported & Guaranteed
We've rigorously tested and certified our SSDs to make sure they work perfectly for you, just like we've done with our industry-leading Mac Memory since 1996. Our SSDs come with a 30-day guarantee, and full access to our customer-support team. There are several steps involved in installing an SSD yourself. We're here to help you along the way and make sure you can enjoy the amazing benefits of SSD. See our SSD installation videos and guides on this page and feel free to call us and we'll walk you through the process.

The Aluminum MacBook DDR3 Machine has a 6GB max out of the box, and can upgraded to 8GB when running Snow Leopard (106.6.6) or later, and the latest Apple Firmware..

To run 8GB in the MacBook Aluminum, find your Boot ROM Version by consulting your System Profiler. Instructions at http://support.apple.com/kb/HT1237.

The correct Boot ROM version for the MacBook 5,1 is MB51.007D.003 or newer. All other model IDs are unaffected. If you do not have this Boot ROM version, please download the latest MacBook EFI Firmware Update 1.4.Â  You must also be running Snow Leopard (10.6.6) or newer to address 8GB on these computers.

Title: Xserve G5 Memory
Body (HTML): The Xserve G5 has eight memory slots, which each hold up to 1GB for a system maximum of 8GB. RAM must be installed in identical matched pairs. Ramjet's 2GB kit contains just such a matched pair of two 1GB DIMMs.

Title: Xserve DDR2-800 Memory
Body (HTML):
The Xserve Intel DDR2-800 uses a new type of memory called an FB-DIMM. There are eight (8) slots, and the FB-DIMMs must be installed in pairs (2x at a time), or to run 256 Bit Addressing they would be installed in matched quads (4x identical modules). The original 1Gig is installed as a pair of two 512mb FB-DIMMs. The system maximum is 32Gigs with the installation of eight (8) 4 Gig FB-DIMMs.

Matched Modules: Ramjet kits contain a matched pair of FB-DIMMs. The kit will consist of identical brand/model/spec IC's. They will be from a single batch, and will have matching series numbers. This ensures perfect compatibility.

256 Bit Addressing: The Xserve Intel is capable of addressing a bank of four (4) FB-DIMMs as a single 256-bit memory bus. Having your memory installed as a matched quad will increase your system performance by 5-10%. The Ramjet 1Gig FB-DIMM kit (2x 512mb) can be installed along with the Apple original 1Gig (2x 512mb) to create a 256 bit quad of four (4) 512mb FB-DIMMs.

Title: Xserve G4 Memory
Body (HTML): The Xserve G4 has four memory slots which can each hold up to 512MB for a system max of 2GB.

Title: PowerMac G5 Original Memory
Body (HTML):
400Mhz DDR vs. 533Mhz DDR2:
Do you have the "Original" G5 that runs 400Mhz DDR memory, or the "Dual Core" G5 that runs 533Mhz DDR2 memory? Refer to our DDR vs. DDR2 Guide.

The G5 "Original" runs 400Mhz DDR memory. These Single Core "Original" G5's can come with either 1 or 2 processor cards and are the Single and Dual G5's. The original has either 4 or 8 memory slots.

Matched Sets:
In order to provide you with optimal performance and stability, all of our G5 kits are configured with matched modules.

Title: PowerMac G5 Dual Core Memory
Body (HTML):
400Mhz DDR vs. 533Mhz DDR2:
Do you have the "Original" G5 that runs 400Mhz DDR memory, or the "Dual Core" G5 that runs 533Mhz DDR2 memory? Refer to our DDR vs. DDR2 Guide.

ECC vs. Non-ECC:
ECC memory is usually used in mission critical applications like servers, but Apple is now making it available to G5 workstations! ECC stands for Error Correction Code. This type of memory uses an extra parity bit to detect and correct some types of memory errors. In order to run ECC, all installed DIMMs must be the ECC type. You can mix ECC and Non-ECC, but the ECC function will be disabled.

The G5 "Dual Core" runs 533Mhz DDR2 memory. These dual core G5s can come with either 1 or 2 processor cards that have two processors on each, and are Dual or Quad G5s. The dual core G5s have 8 memory slots which can each hold a maximum of 2GB, for a system maximum of 16GB.

Matched Sets:
In order to provide you with optimal performance and stability, all of our G5 kits are configured with matched modules.

Title: 4-Bay Firewire RAID Enclosure
Body (HTML):
4-bay Firewire RAID Enclosure

Specifications:
Quad interface 4-bay RAID system is the ultimate solution for fast, safe storage for large amounts of your data. Now it is easy to protect your data from hard drive failure.
This RAID unit contains no drives.
User Friendly:
All RAID functionality is handled by the unit itself, so there is no set-up or ongoing management hassle. Simply plug it in and go! Your computer will treat the RAID system as if it were a normal external hard drive.
The system supports hot-swapping of hard drives, and will automatically rebuild the array when drives are swapped.
No software or IT experience is required.
Large diameter fans and an aluminum enclosure keep the system cool and quiet.
Fully compatible with Time Machine.
Front mounted LEDs for easy monitoring
Quad Interface:
This RAID system supports USB, FireWire 400, FireWire 800, and eSATA. Data transfer is up to 3GB per second.
RAID:
RAID settings are user selectable with switches on the back. Default is RAID 1 (mirroring)
RAID 0 (Striping), RAID 1 (Mirroring), RAID 0+1, RAID 5 (Striping), and RAID 5+ Hotspare (Striping w/ spare drive) are supported.
Raid Terminology Guide

Title: Original iMac Revision A-D Memory
Body (HTML):
The iMac DV and iMac SE machines have processor speeds at 350Mhz or above. These machines are sometimes referred to as the Slot Loading iMacs. This is because the CD-ROM or DVD-ROM drives are in the form of a slot in the front of the machine, rather than a drawer. The iMac DV is notable because of the inclusion of a DVD drive, and Firewire ports.

The iMac Revision A (233Mhz processor) has a memory maximum of 256MB, and the iMac Revisions B-D (266-333Mhz processors) have a memory maximum of 512MB.

Title: iMac DV & SE Memory
Body (HTML):
The iMac DV and iMac SE machines have processor speeds at 350Mhz or above. These machines are sometimes referred to as the Slot Loading iMacs. This is because the CDROM or DVDROM drives are in the form of a slot in the front of the machine, rather than a drawer. The iMac DV is notable because of the inclusion of a DVD drive, and Firewire ports.

Contrary to Apple specification data, the iMac SE and DV are able to use up to 1024MB (1GB). This maximum is acheived with the installation of two 512MB DIMMs.

Title: iMac Flat Panel PC-100/PC-133 SDRAM Memory
Body (HTML):
DDR SDRAM v. PC-100 or PC-133 SDRAM?
If you don't know which version you have, please consult our SDRAM vs. DDR SDRAM guide.

In early 2003, Apple upgraded the iMac Flat Panel's memory controller to run high-speed DDR memory. Earlier models all run standard SDRAM. The PC-100 or PC-133 SDRAM version can run a maximum of 1GB (two 512MB modules.)

User Slot:
The User Slot is the memory slot on the bottom of the machine. When you purchase your new iMac, this is the slot that will be empty. This slot uses a SO-DIMM.
User Slot RAM Installation Guide

Apple Slot:
Your new iMac will arrive with either a 128MB or a 256MB DIMM already installed. In order to upgrade the RAM in this Apple slot, you will need to remove the original RAM first. This slot uses a standard Long-DIMM.
Apple Slot RAM Installation Guide

Title: iMac Flat Panel DDR SDRAM Memory
Body (HTML):
DDR SDRAM v. PC-100 or PC-133 SDRAM?
If you don't know which version you have, please consult our SDRAM vs. DDR SDRAM guide.

In early 2003, Apple upgraded the iMac Flat Panel's memory controller to run high-speed DDR memory. Earlier models all run standard SDRAM. The DDR version can run a maximum of 2GB (two 1GB modules.)

User Slot:
The User Slot is the memory slot on the bottom of the machine. When you purchase your new iMac, this is the slot that will be empty. This slot uses a SO-DIMM.
User Slot RAM Installation Guide

Apple Slot:
Your new iMac will arrive with either a 128MB or a 256MB DIMM already installed. In order to upgrade the RAM in this Apple slot, you will need to remove the original RAM first. This slot uses a standard Long-DIMM.
Apple Slot RAM Installation Guide

Title: iMac G5 iSight Model Memory
Body (HTML):
The newer iMac G5 with the built in iSight camera runs 240pin DDR2 DIMMs. This machine has 512MB soldered on the logic board, and one memory slot. That memory slot can hold a maximum of a 2GB DIMM, for a system maximum of 2.5GB.

Stacked v. non-stacked chips:
A module built from stacked chips takes two RAM wafers and stacks them on top of each other. This makes it possible to build a large module (like a 1GB DIMM) using cheap low density parts. Stacked chip modules are bad because they draw more power, and have inflated error rates caused by heat build-up. Ramjet uses the highest quality non-stacked IC chips.

Title: iMac G5 Original Memory
Body (HTML):
The original iMac G5 has two memory slots, which can hold a maximum of 1GB in each. This memory type is called DDR400 184pin DIMMs. Memory does not have to be installed in matched pairs, but a performance gain is realized if identical sized modules are in both slots. Pairing modules enables Memory Interleaving, which allows your memory controller to address both modules as a single 128bit memory bank.

Stacked v. non-stacked chips:
A module built from stacked chips takes two RAM wafers and stacks them on top of each other. This makes it possible to build a large module (like a 1GB DIMM) using cheap low density parts. Stacked chip modules are bad because they draw more power, and have inflated error rates caused by heat build-up. Ramjet uses the highest quality non-stacked IC chips.

Title: PowerMac G3 Beige Memory
Body (HTML): Contrary to the Apple specification, the PowerMac G3 beige models are able to use a maximum of 768MB in system memory with the installation of three 256MB DIMMs.Â

Title: PowerMac G3 Pro Memory
Body (HTML):
The PowerMac G3 Pro also goes by the names G3 Yosemite, and G3 Blue & White.

Contrary to the Apple specification, the G3 Pro is able to use a maximum of 1024MB (1GB) in system memory.

Ramjet uses the more expensive 16x8 based IC chips in our G3 Pro 256MB modules. This insures better compatibility and performance over the cheaper 32x4 IC's that are used by many memory vendors.

For this application, Ramjet also uses a faster SDRAM type called PC-133, which has been configured to run at 100Mhz in the G3 Pro. This improves reliability, and will give you a small performance improvement over the slower PC-100.

Title: PowerMac G4 PCI Memory
Body (HTML):
The original PCI Yikes version was discontinued in the fall of 1999, and all subsequent models can use the AGP version memory. These later AGP models include the G4 Cube, the G4 Sawtooth, and the G4 Dual Processor.

Maximum RAM: Although it is physically possible to install four 512MB DIMMs, this machine will only recognize a maximum of 1.5GB under OS9. OX10.0 and later are able to recognize a full 2GB.

Title: PowerMac G4 AGP Memory
Body (HTML):
The original PCI Yikes version was discontinued in the fall of 1999, and all subsequent models can use the AGP version memory. These later AGP models include the G4 Cube, the G4 Sawtooth, and the G4 Dual Processor.

Maximum RAM: Although it is physically possible to install four 512MB DIMMs, this machine will only recognize a maximum of 1.5GB under OS9. OX10.0 and later are able to recognize a full 2GB.

Title: PowerMac G4 Quicksilver/G4 2001/G4 Digital Audio Memory
Body (HTML):
This G4 series includes the G4 Quicksilver, the G4 2001, and the G4 Digital Audio model.

The G4 2001 Quicksilver has either three or four memory slots which can each hold up to 512mb. Check your Apple System Profiler, or open and view the inside of your machine to determine which configuration you have. Or, you may call Ramjet, and one of our memory experts will assist you.

PC-133 Compatibility: Older 100Mhz G4's [G4 AGP, G4 Cube, old G4 Dual] [NOT G4 PCI] are capable of using these PC-133 G4 DIMMs.

Apple recommends JEDEC MO-161-D compliant RAM for this series.

Title: PowerMac G4 DDR 'Mirror Drive Door' Memory
Body (HTML):
The G4 DDR series has four memory slots which can each hold up to 512mb for a system max of 2GB.

DDR400 Speed & Stability: All PowerMac G4 DDR models are capable of running high performance PC-3200 DDR400 SDRAM. PC-3200 is the fastest form of RAM available for the G4 DDR, and it is the part that Ramjet recommends. Using this type of RAM will also reduce memory errors thanks to the more advanced fabrication techniques used in its production.

Title: Xserve DDR3-1066 Memory
Body (HTML):
The Xserve DDR3-1066 comes in two versions, the 4-core and the 8-core. The 4-core has 6 DIMM slots, and it upgradable to a maximum of 24GB with the installation of 6x 4GB modules (2x 12GB kits). The 8-core has 12 slots, and it is upgradable to a maximum of 48GB with the installation of 12x 4GB modules (4x 12GB kits). Since the new Xseve runs a "Tri-Channel" memory interface, memory MUST be installed in matched sets of three at a time.

Matched Modules: The new Xserve Intel DDR3-1066 runs a Tri-Channel memory interface. The Ramjet kits for the Xserve DDR3-1066 contain a matched set (3x) of DIMMs. The kit will consist of identical brand/model/spec IC's. They will be from a single batch, and will have matching series numbers. This ensures maximum performance, and perfect compatibility.

Title: PowerBook G4 Titanium Memory
Body (HTML):
The PowerBook G4 Titanium model has two memory slots which run PC-133 SO-DIMMs. The Titanium can recognize a maximum of 1Gig (1024mb). You can reach that maximum with the installation of two (2) 512mb SO-DIMMs.

Stacked v. non-stacked chips: A module built from stacked chips takes two RAM wafers and stacks them on top of each other. This makes it possible to build a large module (like a 512mb SDRAM SO-DIMM) using cheap low density parts. Stacked chip modules are bad because they draw more power, and have heat build-up problems. Ramjet only uses Lower Power Consumption non-stacked IC chips.

Title: PowerBook G4 Aluminum (DDR2) Memory
Body (HTML):
The PowerBook G4 Aluminum has used two different types of PowerBook RAM during it's model run: DDR2 and DDR. These two memory types are not compatible with each other, so it is important to find out which type your PowerBook runs before you order. The earlier PowerBook G4 Aluminum models run DDR. The newer PowerBook G4 Aluminum released on Oct. 20, 2005 run DDR2.

For assistance in finding your RAM type, please look at our DDR vs. DDR2 Guide.


12" Model: One memory slot that can be upgraded with up to a 1Gig PC-2700 SO-DIMM. The original 128mb or 256mb that comes with this PowerBook is soldered on the main logic board, and is not removable.

15" and 17" Models: Two memory slots. The models released on Oct. 20, 2005 (M996LL/A and M9970LL/A) run DDR2, and the earlier models run DDR.

Bus Slewing: Some models of PowerBook G4 Aluminum use this feature which lowers the voltage to the memory when the PowerBook is on battery power. This conserves power. However, this also means that you need a special Bus Slewing compatible SO-DIMM that can handle an undervoltage properly. Ramjet SO-DIMMs for the PowerBook G4 Aluminum have the low voltage feature, and therefore the Ramjet modules here are Bus Slewing compatible.
